lines.text: On Technical Assistance Participants Visiting the U. S.
INSTRUCTIONS TO PARTICIPANTS: Prepare this form on a typewriter in English. In order to prevent delay and to assist in
planning your program, answer every question clearly and completely. If more space is needed, use a blank sheet of typing paper.
Write your name, country, and date of birth on each sheet.
1. NAME (Last or Surname in capital letters)
6. PLEASE PROVIDE THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION FOR YOUR SPOUSE, YOUR FATHER, AND YOUR MOTHER
PERSON AT HOME TO BE NOTIFIED IN CASE OF EMERGENCY (Name, Address, and Relationship)
8. PERSON IN U. S. TO BE NOTIFIED IN CASE OF EMERGENCY (Name, Address, and Relationship)
9. HAVE YOU EVER BEEN IN THE U. S.? IF SO, WHEN, WHERE, FOR HOW LONG AND FOR WHAT PURPOSE?
April-May 1955 Atlantic City, New York, Washington -3 weeks - Official visit PASB.
June 1952 to December 1953 - New York . 2 1/2 yrs - Post Graduate training
. HAVE YOU EVER TRAVELLED TO COUNTRIES OTHER THAN U. S., IF SO, WHEN, WHERE, AND FOR HOW LONG? (Include travel
for educational purposes as well as pleasure)
As of January 1954 have been travelling through Central Am. & Panama on official duty.
11. HAVE YOU PARTICIPATED IN OR APPLIED FOR ANY OTHER U. S., U. N., OR PRIVATE TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE ACTIVITY?
Actually working as nutritionist at PASB, assigned to INCAP.
. LIST MEMBERSHIP IN EDUCATIONAL, PROFESSIONAL, AGRICULTURAL, LABOR OR OTHER TYPES OF ORGANIZATIONS AND SOCIETIES OF A SIMILAR
NATURE. IF YOU HOLD OFFICE IN ANY OF THESE ORGANIZATIONS, SPECIFY.
El Colegio Medico de Guatemala. Member.
Society for Research in Child Development. Member.
STUDIED, OR WORKED ON. E. G. MILK MARKETING, ETC.
BE SPECIFIC. INDICATE FIELD OF ENDEAVOR, CROP, PRODUCT, PROCESS, TECHNIQUE, ETC. TO BE OBSERVED,
Post graduate courses in biochemistry and nutrition. University of Vanderbilt.
Attend Public Health School so as to obtain the Master in Public Health degree.
